ated at the confluence of imperial endowment practices and Ottoman food supply policies, while also exemplifying the role of imperial women as benefactors. Through its operations, the imaret linked imperial Ottoman and local Palestinian interests, integrating urban and rural economies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aEndowmentsxHistoryxJerusalem. 0aEndowmentszJerusalemxHistory. 0aWaqfxHistoryxJerusalem. 0aWaqfzJerusalemxHistory. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Islam. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Philanthropy & Charity.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791488768423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791488768/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles